If you want to filter on &quot;descriptions&quot; you need to  change your mapping from object to [nested type](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/nested.html).
Object type is stored as flat fields so it not possible to filter them
ex. when description is of type object fields under it are stored as description.locale etc.. 

 Below query will return all modelA which have description in french and french description will be present in [inner_hits](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/search-request-body.html#request-body-search-inner-hits)
````
GET /product/_search
{
  &quot;query&quot;: {
    &quot;bool&quot;: {
      &quot;must&quot;: [
        {
          &quot;term&quot;: {
            &quot;model&quot;: &quot;modelA&quot;
          }
        },
        {
          &quot;nested&quot;: {
            &quot;path&quot;: &quot;descriptions&quot;,
            &quot;query&quot;: {
              &quot;match&quot;: {
                &quot;descriptions.locale&quot;: &quot;fr&quot;
              }
            },
            &quot;inner_hits&quot;: {}
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
````

